Algeria Trade Surplus Widens 27% in First Four Months, APS Says

-- B y   S a l a h   S l i m a n i
-- 
2011-05-23T09:53:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/algeria-trade-surplus-widens-27-in-first-four-months-aps-says.html
Algeria’s trade surplus widened 27
percent in the first four months of the year as oil prices
increased, the state-run APS news agency reported.  The surplus widened to $8.6 billion, the Algiers-based
agency said, citing the customs agency’s National Centre of
Informatics and Statistics. Exports increased 16 percent to
$23.6 billion while imports rose 11 percent to $15 billion, it
said. Oil accounted for 97 percent of exports.  To contact the reporter on this story:
